--------------------------------------------------------------------------
	OSACrew Version: 6.0.25 (June 27, 2026)
	
	   Usage: 
	
	   ;osacrew setup                       Opens the setup window
	   ;osacrew underway                    Will get your ship underway
	   ;osacrew underway anchor             Will raise the anchor
	   ;osacrew underway sails              Will lower your sails
	   ;osacrew navigation                  Will begin port to port travel
	   ;osacrew repair                      Will begin damage control on the ship
	   ;osacrew cannons                     Will man the cannons of your choosing
	   ;osacrew swap                        Enables you to swap commands with ease
	   ;osacrew orders                      Will await your commander to announce location of ship then board ship
	   ;osacrew disembark                   Will depart the crew at the next convienent location
	   ;osacrew settings                    Will show current settings
	   ;osacrew profile                     Will save/load profiles for different commander settings
	
	   This is a companion to OSACommander. It is ran on your crew members to complete simple tasks on the ship including combat. 
	   Enjoy 
	
	   ~Peggyanne 
	    PS: feel free to send me any bugs via discord Bait#4376 and I'll try my best to fix them.
	 
	 Change Log:
	 
          January 25, 2026 - Added Anti-Poaching Command For Toggle and Changed Name of Setup Method To Prevent Cross Script Errors.
          January 26, 2026 - Fixed Issue With Empath Commanders Stalling During Boarding and Fixed Issues With Sinking Ship Via Cannons.
          February 1, 2026 - Updated Yaml Read/Write Methods To Include FLOCK Operations To Prevent Data Corruption.
         February 13, 2026 - Rewrote YAML Config and GTK3 Using AI.
              May 16, 2026 - Cannons tab: duty and cannon checkboxes are mutually exclusive. Gunners Man Your Irons encounter added windedsails check. winded_sails now waits 90 seconds 
                             between passes with 1-second stop detection.
              May 17, 2026 - Replaced old no_file/needfile dependency check with check_dependencies. Added osasail_watch, osacannon_watch and osa_migrate to dependency list with 
                             correct authors. Fixed gunner methods going dormant due to stale XML hand state. Added police_cannon_balls before damage control. Increased dothistimeout 
                             in gunner methods from 5s to 10s; added stall counter to gunner_cycle.
              May 18, 2026 - Reverted Wind Sails / Use Cannons mutual exclusion; both can now be checked independently. Cannon encounters no longer call wind the sails. 
                             Rewrote gunner_get_balls/load/fire with correct linear flow: pile -> hold floor -> deck floor -> out of balls. Fire-both duty reloads from 
                             deck floor and re-fires within gunner_fire_cannon. Fire-only duty now pauses 3 seconds when cannon not yet loaded. Fixed cannon_should_stop? 
                             always reloading @crew_data so stop flags break the cycle immediately.
              May 19, 2026 - Fixed cannon fire and ship detection triggers re-launching osacommander mid-encounter; both now reload @crew_data before checking boarding flag.
              May 20, 2026 - resource_check now reads all data from resource.lic YAML (weekly, total, suffused, bonus); removed old quiet_command resource parsing entirely.
              May 21, 2026 - gunner_out_of_balls now sends lnet crew notification when cannon_engage is true. gunner_boarded routes to helm (not combat) when out of balls 
                             during cannon-only encounter.
              May 22, 2026 - Removed unused Win32Sound/winmm audio code that was crashing on macOS.
              May 22, 2026 - Added profiles support (osacrew profiles folder); Save As, Load, Delete via GUI matching osacombat profile logic.
              May 23, 2026 - Added crew_cast_sever, crew_sever_cleanup methods and Begin Sever/Sever Spellup Complete lnet triggers. Fixed
                             sever spell callout to read sever_spell_1 through sever_spell_4 from osacombat YAML. Crew casts known sever
                             spells on requesters, then waits for Sever Spellup Complete signal before stopping non-preference spells.
                             Cleanup uses severance.lic logic; group spells and arcane circles always exempt. Fixed @combat_data
                             references to use osacombat_data YAML loader so sever spell prefs load correctly without osacombat running.
             June 27, 2026 - Added "Take Us To Hallowed Ground" crew channel handler for medical officer. When commander broadcasts
                             the command with the medical officer's name, the medical officer pauses osacombat and ecure, releases
                             any prepared spell, casts Spell[220] (Word of Return), then unpauses ecure. Added "Take Us Back"
                             handler; medical officer waits RT, stands, moves out, then transfers group lead back to commander.
=end

def lnet_crew(msg)
	if @crew_data["crew"].nil? || @crew_data["crew"].strip.empty?
		respond "--- OSACrew: Crew channel is not defined. Please run ;osacrew setup and set your Crew Channel before continuing."
		return
	end
	LNet.send_message(attr = { 'type' => 'channel', 'channel' => @crew_data["crew"] }, msg)
end

# Checks for required scripts and prompts the user to download any that are missing.
# deps is an array of hashes: [{ name: 'scriptname', author: 'author' }, ...]
def check_dependencies(script_label, deps)
	deps.each do |dep|
		next if Script.exists?(dep[:name])
		respond ""
		respond " =========================================================="
		respond "  #{script_label} requires: #{dep[:name]}"
		respond "  This script could not be found in your script folder."
		respond " =========================================================="
		respond "  Would you like to download it now?"
		respond "    1. Yes - download #{dep[:name]} and continue"
		respond "    2. No  - exit (#{script_label} cannot run without it)"
		respond " =========================================================="
		respond "  Please select an option - ;send <#>"
		respond ""
		clear
		answer = nil
		answer = get until answer.to_s.strip =~ /^[12]$/
		if answer.strip == "1"
			respond "  Downloading #{dep[:name]}..."
			args = ["download", dep[:name]]
			args << "--author=#{dep[:author]}" if dep[:author]
			start_script("repository", args)
			wait_until { !running?("repository") }
			respond "  Download complete."
			respond ""
		else
			respond "  Very well. Please restart #{script_label} once you have #{dep[:name]} installed."
			exit
		end
	end
end

